    = authority_boundary: accepted_external_and_model_only
    = next_legitimate_motion: model_calibration_or_public_synthesis

& [InterpretationRule] is the morphology boundary
  + [rule_001] is local structure can be meaningful even when bridge proof is absent
  + [rule_002] is naming bridge type improves navigation but does not reduce unresolved lock mass
  + [rule_003] is future inquiry should match its motion type to the bridge type
  + [rule_004] is repeated inquiry without a matching theorem, validation, or model target becomes churn
  + [rule_005] is model scoring should keep bridge failures visible rather than smoothing them into coherence

& [CuriousPeriphery] is the next research edge
  + [question] is whether bridge types can predict the responsible next motion before a theorem target appears
  + [candidate_next_tool] is BridgeObstructionModeSelector
  + [tool_need] is conditional
    = reason: create only if future walks repeatedly need to choose between theorem_target, validation_target, model_calibration, public_synthesis, source_boundary, and quiet_watch

& [CurrentReading] is the walking-protocol update
  + [selected_mode] is tooling
  + [meaning] is the recurring bridge-failure pattern has become a project-local research object
  + [proof_boundary] is unchanged
  + [next_walk_candidate] is apply morphology to select the next legitimate motion or quiet-watch if no bridge-specific motion appears
